<subSubSection box="[136,535,1706,1733]" pageId="12" pageNumber="111" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,535,1706,1733]" box="[136,535,1706,1733]" pageId="12" pageNumber="111">
<heading box="[136,535,1706,1733]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="12" pageNumber="111" reason="3">
<taxonomicName authority="Sprengel (1824: 132)" authorityName="Sprengel" authorityPageNumber="132" authorityYear="1824" box="[136,531,1706,1733]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,282,1706,1733]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="111">Merostachys</emphasis>
Sprengel (1824: 132)
</taxonomicName>
.
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="111" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,1778,2093]" box="[136,740,1778,1805]" pageId="12" pageNumber="111">
<typeStatus box="[136,209,1779,1805]" pageId="12" pageNumber="111">TYPE</typeStatus>
:— 
<taxonomicName authority="Sprengel (1824: 249)" authorityName="Sprengel" authorityPageNumber="249" authorityYear="1824" box="[242,735,1778,1804]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis box="[242,487,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="111">Merostachys speciosa</emphasis>
Sprengel (1824: 249)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,1778,2093]" pageId="12" pageNumber="111">
Plants cespitose. Culms homomorphic, scandent at maturity, often drooping from trees, 
<quantity box="[1193,1280,1814,1841]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="111" unit="m" value="11.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="2.0">2–20 m</quantity>
tall, infra- and supranodal bands of trichomes absent or present. Branch complement apsidate (fan-shaped), few to many branches, sometimes branches branched, without thorns. Culm leaves and foliage leaves clearly distinct. Culm leaves not clearly differentiated along the culm, with reflexed blades, narrower than the sheath summit, sheath fimbriae present, not fused. Foliage leaf sheaths with fimbriae at the apex or not, translucent swelling absent, outer ligule present, blades lanceolate or ovate-lanceolate, midnerve not prominent. Synflorescences a terminal raceme, pectinate; spikelets sessile or on short pedicels, bisexual, glumes 2, anthecium smooth (as far as known), the apex of rachilla extension bearing a rudimentary anthecium. Fruit a nucoid caryopsis, hilum conspicuous or not.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="112" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,158,361]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sprengel" authorityYear="1824" box="[189,331,158,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,331,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Merostachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a scandent woody bamboo genus with the branch complement apsidate, culm leaves with reflexed blades, narrower than the sheath summit, sheath fimbriae present and free, synflorescences terminal and racemose, pectinate and the caryopsis nucoid (
<bibRefCitation author="McClure, F. A." box="[531,697,229,255]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" pagination="1 - 148" refId="ref25619" refString="McClure, F. A. (1973) Genera of bamboos native to the new world (Gramineae: Bambusoideae). Smithsonian Contributions to Botany 9: 1 - 148. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 123328" type="journal article" year="1973">McClure 1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vinicius-Silva, R. &amp; Parma, D. F. &amp; Jesus-Costa, C. &amp; Clark, L. G. &amp; Santos-Goncalves, A. P." box="[706,994,229,255]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" pagination="1 - 39" refId="ref27813" refString="Vinicius-Silva, R., Parma, D. F., Jesus-Costa, C., Clark, L. G. &amp; Santos-Goncalves, A. P. (2018) Merostachys Spreng. (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Bambuseae: Arthrostylidiinae) na Mata Atlantica do Estado de Minas Gerais, Brasil. Hoehnea 45 (1): 1 - 39. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / 2236 - 8906 - 29 / 2017" type="journal article" year="2018">
Vinicius-Silva 
<emphasis box="[872,927,229,255]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). The genus has 57 species in Central and South America (
<bibRefCitation author="Kellogg, E. A." box="[317,475,264,291]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" refId="ref25159" refString="Kellogg, E. A. (2015) The Families and Genera of Vascular Plants Volume XIII. Flowering Plants Monocots: Poaceae. Springer International Publishing, Switzerland, 413 pp." type="book" year="2015">Kellogg 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vinicius-Silva, R. &amp; Parma, D. F. &amp; Jesus-Costa, C. &amp; Clark, L. G. &amp; Santos-Goncalves, A. P." box="[485,773,264,290]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" pagination="1 - 39" refId="ref27813" refString="Vinicius-Silva, R., Parma, D. F., Jesus-Costa, C., Clark, L. G. &amp; Santos-Goncalves, A. P. (2018) Merostachys Spreng. (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Bambuseae: Arthrostylidiinae) na Mata Atlantica do Estado de Minas Gerais, Brasil. Hoehnea 45 (1): 1 - 39. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / 2236 - 8906 - 29 / 2017" type="journal article" year="2018">
Vinícius-Silva 
<emphasis box="[652,708,264,290]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vinicius-Silva, R. &amp; Clark, L. G. &amp; Fregonezi, J. N. &amp; Santos-Goncalves, A. P." box="[784,857,264,290]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" pagination="453 - 461" refId="ref27574" refString="Vinicius-Silva, R., Clark, L. G., Fregonezi, J. N. &amp; Santos-Goncalves, A. P. (2021 a) Clarifying the identity of Merostachys speciosa (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Bambuseae), type species of the genus, through redescription and second-step lectotypification. Kew Bulletin 76: 453 - 461. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 021 - 09958 - z" type="journal article" year="2021">2021a</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[905,976,264,290]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 50 species occur in Amazon, Cerrado and Mata Atlântica domains (
<bibRefCitation author="Vinicius-Silva, R. &amp; Clark, L. G. &amp; Shirasuna, R. T. &amp; Goncalves, A. P. S. &amp; Filgueiras, T. S." box="[417,707,299,325]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" refId="ref27481" refString="Vinicius-Silva, R., Clark, L. G., Shirasuna, R. T., Goncalves, A. P. S. &amp; Filgueiras, T. S. (in memoriam) (2020) Merostachys in Flora do Brasil 2020, Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro state, Brazil. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 13316 (accessed 9 October 2021)." type="url" year="2020">
Vinícius-Silva 
<emphasis box="[586,642,299,325]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vinicius-Silva, R &amp; Clark, L. G. &amp; Fregonezi, J. N. &amp; Goncalves, A. P." box="[718,791,299,325]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" pagination="167 - 177" refId="ref27654" refString="Vinicius-Silva, R, Clark, L. G., Fregonezi, J. N. &amp; Goncalves, A. P. (2021 b) Two new species of Merostachys (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Bambuseae) from the Brazilian Atlantic Forest in the states of Espirito Santo and Minas Gerais. Brittonia 73: 167 - 177. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12228 - 020 - 09642 - 9" type="journal article" year="2021">2021b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vinicius-Silva, R. &amp; Fregonezi, J. N. &amp; Clark, L. G. &amp; Santos-Goncalves, A. P." box="[801,875,299,325]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref27733" refString="Vinicius-Silva, R., Fregonezi, J. N., Clark, L. G. &amp; Santos-Goncalves, A. P. (2021 c) Recircumscription of three Merostachys species (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Bambuseae: Arthrostylidiinae) and description of a new species from the Brazilian Atlantic Forest. Nordic Journal of Botany 39 (8): 1 - 13. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / njb. 02974" type="journal article" year="2021">2021c</bibRefCitation>
). In the Serra do Cachimbo, it is represented by one species, a new taxon here described.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
